topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Guide to Becoming a Successful Raid Leader(long)</span><hr size=1> Posts like this, and the general good attitude I see on this board, convinced me to start a monk :-)<br><br>Pet stuff:<br><br>Pets are non-aggro when not fighting now, unless the owner is attacked.  A pet that gets lost can wander all over a zone, and never aggro anything.  Once a pet is fighting, it can get aggro.  If the mage has Pet Hold, then you can beat on a pet or its master and it won't fight back.  Pets won't be getting any exp anymore either.  If anyone other than the pet does even 1 point of dmg, the pet gets no exp.<br><br>VI is trying to fix it so pets can't break mez.  Maybe they have...  So far even if I order pet to break a mez, it's not happened;  the pet even tells you that it won't do it.  Supposedly if the pet is casting its spell (a pretty quick cast) at the moment a mob is mezzed, it will continue casting and break the mez.  I think pets are better than players now at not breaking mez.<br><br>The AOE thing is the big problem.  The owner (way in the back!) gets hit for a tiny bit and the pet takes the offensive.  If you don't have Pet Hold, you need to be fast on the back off key, or have your earthen boots hot keyed.  Hit that, you go invis to animals, and the pet is gone, no matter where it is.  IMO this problem is the worst potential downfall of pets, and the Mage class is a big letdown without the pet.  It requires everyone to place TOO much trust in the pet owner.<br><br>As a RL you should know that when you say &quot;no pets&quot; you put a knife in the Mage's gut.  At least say why, in that situation.  It sounds like you are a person who values every player he meets, so you are probably as fair as you can be already.  Pet Hold should be a level 50 skill, not such a hard-to-get AA skill.<br><br>Oh, and all you RL's; you have to have the mage in the puller's group for Call of the Hero to work!  Recently had a L60 RL/puller tell me to CoH him.  He had not put a mage in his group...<br><br>Loraff, 55 Mage<br>Up-and-coming 17 Monk<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=philomath>Philomath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/27/02 5:48:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1044.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Guide to Becoming a Successful Raid Leader(long)</span><hr size=1>    Sometimes you need to outline the usage of DOTs before a raid.  DOT corpse poofing has been fixed for anyone who remembers the bug.  However a DOTed mob cannot be mezzed.  This can pose a problem on raids.  Most times you are not going to try to offload a boss mob (mezz him and switch targets), due to an add or something, just be aware that if he is dotted you will not be able to mezz him.  Also be aware that Necro snares have a DOT component so if they are snaring things those things cannot be mezzed.  DOTs are a valuable addition for killing mobs that take over a minute or two to kill, but when the the *&amp;%^ hits the fan and you want the chanter to lock things down be aware that those those mobs are not going to lock down.  <br><br>   I have been to raids with my Necro where DOTs were not allowed at all.  I have also been to &quot;pickup raids&quot; where due to people not using assist button there were multiple dotted mobs when the chanter tried to lock things down, bad wipeout.  <br><br>   As with the case of Mages and there pets if there is a hard and fast rule no DOTS and your make any Necros Twitch B1tches they are not going to be very happy.  <br><br>Jabe Rwoky<br>Level 50 Monk-in-training<br>Rynz NReap<br>Level 51 Necro<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uwaldena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Waldena</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.sonic.net/knightstribunal/images/flamedot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/29/02 6:53:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1044.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Guide to Becoming a Successful Raid Leader(long)</span><hr size=1> With the recent changes, the only way for a pet to aggro a mob is the pet owner issuing a /pet attack command, or the pet getting hit by an AE (it will also aggro if the pet owner is meleed, but that doesnt matter because the mob is already aggroed on the owner when this happens).<br><br>The only time i would not allow pets is when mobs with AEs are being split in AE range of the raid.  Even then, the pet owner has a few seconds to press /pet back off after each AE to keep the pet from charging the MoBs.<br><br>If the person has /pet hold, then they should be able to use a pet whenever they want.<br><br>They only way for for a pet to break a mez is if the pet starts casting a spell before mez has landed, and the spell lands after mez has landed.  This will almost never happen because pet spells cast almost instantly (99% of the time the Pet Beginis to Cast a spell message and the spell landing message will be listed in the same second in a log file).  It seems like the spells have a 2 second cast time when you watch the pet, but that is because after the spell lands the pet cannot begin meleeing again for 2 seconds.  Durring those 2 second the pet just sits there, so it looks like the pet is still casting the spell (especially because the animation from the spell effect is probably not finished yet).<br><br>There are some mobs where pets will be made useless because of AEs, or will die quick because of AEs and it is not worth summoning a pet, but it's up to the pet owner because it wont hurt the raid. <p><font size=1 face="verdana"><center>[60 <a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower">Arch Mage</a>] <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=13177" target="_blank">Waldena</a> (Human) < <a href="http://pub80.ezboard.com/btranscended">Transcended</a> > SERVER: <a href="http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg">The Tribunal</a><br><i>"Summon someone who gives a damn"</i>-Pirotes<br>Golf is not a sport</center></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uwaldena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Waldena</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.sonic.net/knightstribunal/images/flamedot.gif" BORDER=0> at: 8/29/02 6:57:54 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usarginthemonk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sarginthemonk</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://info.winamp.com/winamp/images/ebay.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 116<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/29/02 9:06:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1044.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Guide to Becoming a Successful Raid Leader(long)</span><hr size=1> Changed pet rules around a little. <p><table width="490"><tr><td> <img src="http://lukang.homestead.com/files/untitled1.jpg" width="374" height="250" hspace="5" vspace="3" alt="Me"> </td><td align="middle" font size=2 face=arial color=grey><div align="center"><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#999999" size="2">Sargin